e fashion his history of coagulopathy, the patient is discussed with Dr. X and he is admitted for orders.  Also we will consult Dr. Y, see orders for further.',46,'Bennett Sharpe','1444-Hematuria - Consult.txt'),(117,0,'Generic description Mon Mar 17 14:58:56 MDT 2014','2012-05-26 16:47:22','General Medical Clinic11/05/2008 13:00CCFollow up DiabetesSubjectivePatient came in earlier today and requested orders for labs he is due for.  He was fasting for labs today.DepressionThe patient indicates his mood is much improved since increasing Citalopram to 40 mg daily and he would like to continue the medication at this dose.  He indicates he has sufficient energy throughout the day and is sleeping well through the night.  He has been seeing psychology for counseling and thinks this is helping as well.Diabetes mellitus type 2The patient reports being compliant with use of Metformin.  He is exercising occasionally (walks 1-3 miles once or twice a week).   He admits to eating too many sugary and fatty foods on the weekends but does well with his diet on the week days.HypertensionNo light headedness.Coronary Artery DiseaseNo angina or shortness of breath.Benign prostatic hyperplasiaThe pt reports waking to urinate at most once per night.AllergiesNKDAPMHHYPERTENSION NOSDiabetes MellitusCoronary Artery DiseaseBenign prostatic hyperplasiaHyperlipidemiaDepressionPSurgHxAppendectomy at age 7 years. FamHxMother: Diabetes Mellitus Father: Coronary Artery DiseaseGrandfather: Dementia SocHxPrevious smoker, 1/2 ppd X 10 years (5 pack year history), quit 30 years ago.Occasional alcohol use (no more than 3 drinks per day)No illicit drug use everDivorced, no children, works at hardware store.MedicationsCitalopram 40 mg PO daily #90, 3 refillsMetformin 500 mg PO BID #180, 3 refillsHydrochlorothiazide 12.5 mg PO daily #90, 3 refillsLisinopril 20 mg PO daily #90, 3 refillsMetoprolol 25 mg PO BID #180, 3 refillsAspirin 81 mg PO daily #90, 3 refillsSimvastatin 40 mg PO daily #90, 3 refillsTams